    "description": "Right now the gadget frontend tests fail with the following error in python3:\r\n\r\n```\r\ngoldbaum at ROUS2 in ~/Documents/yt-hg-python3 on yt?^\r\n\u263f nosetests3 frontends.gadget\r\nE\r\n======================================================================\r\nERROR: yt.frontends.gadget.tests.test_outputs.test_GadgetDataset\r\n----------------------------------------------------------------------\r\nTraceback (most recent call last):\r\n  File \"/usr/local/lib/python3.4/site-packages/nose/case.py\", line 198, in runTest\r\n    self.test(*self.arg)\r\n  File \"/Users/goldbaum/Documents/yt-hg-python3/yt/frontends/gadget/tests/test_outputs.py\", line 55, in test_GadgetDataset\r\n    assert isinstance(data_dir_load(isothermal_bin, kwargs=iso_kwargs),\r\n  File \"/Users/goldbaum/Documents/yt-hg-python3/yt/utilities/answer_testing/framework.py\", line 287, in data_dir_load\r\n    ds = load(ds_fn, *args, **kwargs)\r\n  File \"/Users/goldbaum/Documents/yt-hg-python3/yt/convenience.py\", line 72, in load\r\n    return candidates[0](*args, **kwargs)\r\n  File \"/Users/goldbaum/Documents/yt-hg-python3/yt/frontends/gadget/data_structures.py\", line 107, in __init__\r\n    super(GadgetDataset, self).__init__(filename, dataset_type)\r\n  File \"/Users/goldbaum/Documents/yt-hg-python3/yt/data_objects/static_output.py\", line 192, in __init__\r\n    self._parse_parameter_file()\r\n  File \"/Users/goldbaum/Documents/yt-hg-python3/yt/frontends/gadget/data_structures.py\", line 141, in _parse_parameter_file\r\n    hvals = self._get_hvals()\r\n  File \"/Users/goldbaum/Documents/yt-hg-python3/yt/frontends/gadget/data_structures.py\", line 133, in _get_hvals\r\n    hvals = read_record(f, self._header_spec)\r\n  File \"/Users/goldbaum/Documents/yt-hg-python3/yt/utilities/fortran_utils.py\", line 292, in read_record\r\n    vals = list(struct.unpack(net_format, f.read(size)))\r\n  File \"/usr/local/Cellar/python3/3.4.3_2/Frameworks/Python.framework/Versions/3.4/lib/python3.4/codecs.py\", line 319, in decode\r\n    (result, consumed) = self._buffer_decode(data, self.errors, final)\r\nUnicodeDecodeError: 'utf-8' codec can't decode byte 0x8f in position 78: invalid start byte\r\n\r\n----------------------------------------------------------------------\r\nRan 1 test in 2.734s\r\n\r\nFAILED (errors=1)\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe fix in this PR is to explicitly open the file handle for binary reading, since the default is UTF-8 in python3.",
